records.addlTxt:
08:34 AM Defendant Collin K Barron in court with attorney J Andrew Herbers.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for plea and sentencing in 22CM342 and 22CM670.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In case 22CM342: 
  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 2,  Court finds defendant guilty.
  Counts 1 & 3 are Dismissed and read in.

In case 22CM670:
  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty.
  Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.

State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the Court. 

Court orders the following:
In case 22CM342: 

SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation:   15 MONTHS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*No violent contact with:  any of the victims; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*20 Hours of Community Service; 

RESTITUTION:  $325 to Lad Lake (Restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
COSTS:  $243
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations. If the Defendant violates any terms of his/her probation, or has any condition time imposed, the Court will deem that the conditions precedent necessary for the conditional grant of Expunction have not been met and therefore Expunction is denied. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.

